gomodel:SYNGO_5297  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: overexpression of GFP-Rac3 showed localization to dendritic shaft and spines (co-localizatoin with endogenous Homer) in 4DIV hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 4: double knockout of Rac1 and Rac3 leads to severely impaired postsynapse formation in 4DIV hippocampal neurons, which could be rescued by overexpression of either GFP-Rac3 or GFP-Rac1.\n\nauthors summarise;\n\"The re-expression of either GTPase significantly and strongly increased the size of mushroom spines, as detected by measuring the area of their heads (Fig 4D): Rac1 and Rac3 expression induced a 3.3-fold (P < 0.001) and 5.4-fold (P < 0.001) increase in average spine head area respectively, compared to the average spine head area for the few spines formed by the double KO neurons.\n\nInterestingly, as already observed after overexpressing either GTPase in the WT neurons, Rac3 has a stronger effect compared to Rac1 on the size of the spines. In the case of re-expression of the Rac3 GTPase in double KO cells the effects were more evident compared to its overexpression in WT cells that express endogenous Rac3. The increase of the mean spine head area induced by Rac3 was 1.6-fold that induced by the re-expression of Rac1 (P < 0.001).\n\nAltogether these data indicate that the re-expression of either Rac1 or Rac3 was sufficient to re-establish the formation of dendritic spines, and that Rac3 promoted the formation of larger spines.\". Experimental description: The Rac1/3 double knockout in mice was followed by overexpression of either Rac1 and Rac3. The exact sequences are of GFP-Rac1 and GFP-Rac3 are not shown, but are assumed to be mouse sequences." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5297" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

